sql:
SELECT description, status
FROM tms_sequences
WHERE sequence_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM tms_sequences
WHERE ic_id = 902 AND status = 'Failed';

external_knowledge:
- TCK cycles refer to the clock cycles in tests used for evaluating the quality and functionality of IC components;
- Readback bits are part of the data collected during these tests to verify the correct operation of the components;
- TDI signals (Test Data In) are inputs used in the testing process, where 'X' indicates a 'don't care' condition.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(sequence_id) AS total_completed_sequences
FROM tms_sequences
WHERE status = 'Completed';

SELECT status
FROM tms_sequences
WHERE status = 'Failed';

SELECT COUNT(tdi_id) AS total_signals, description
FROM tdi_signals
GROUP BY description;

SELECT number_of_cycles
FROM tck_cycles
WHERE step_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(readback_id) AS readback_count
FROM readback_bits
WHERE number_of_bits < 0 AND description = 'Indicates readback of all bits except the last one';

SELECT TRIM(description) AS trimmed_description
FROM tms_signals
WHERE tms_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- IC components refer to Integrated Circuit components being tested; 
- Latest test results are determined by the most recent timestamp; 
- Corresponding latest issues are determined by the most recent timestamp for each IC component.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(issue_id) AS total_issues
FROM issues
WHERE ic_id = 1;
